The paper deals with inferring player valuations from observed data in auctions, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of no-regret learning, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper applies its techniques to a dataset from Microsoft's sponsored search ad auction system, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and electronic commerce (cs.EC).
